==== Configuration Settings ====

{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.DisplayConfigurationWidget
| clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.provider.R2RMLProvider
}}

The R2RML Provider uses an R2RML engine (e.g. by default DB2Triples) to map relational data to RDF. 

Starting from a [[Help:TableDataSources| tabular data source]], the [[Help:R2RMLMappings| R2RML mapping]] can be defined. The R2RML provider then uses the tabular data source and the corresponding mapping, and feeds the configuration into the R2RML materializer engine (e.g., DB2Triples by default).

See [[Help:DataSources]] for a full integration example

Note that the [https://appcenter.fluidops.com/resource/?uri=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fluidops.com%2Fapplication%2Fontop ontop] integration can be used as an alternative R2RML materializer.




